    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a spirit level calibration device made by Gebroeders Caminada, Rotterdam, a prominent Dutch instrument-making firm of Italian origin (active 1856–c. 1920). The device is a bench-top apparatus used to test and calibrate spirit level vials used in surveying leveling instruments. Its production period (1882–1898) coincides with the Netherlands' Eerste Nauwkeurigheidswaterpassing (First Precision Leveling Survey, 1875–1885), which demanded rigorously calibrated instruments.",
